paperparcel

Annotation Type Adapter


  • @Documented
 @Retention(value=SOURCE)
 @Target(value={})
public @interface Adapter
    Used in conjunction with ProcessorConfig to add a custom TypeAdapter to PaperParcel's type system.

    • Required Element Summary

      Required Elements 
      Modifier and Type Required Element and Description
      java.lang.Class<? extends TypeAdapter> value
      The TypeAdapter class to register into PaperParcel's type system.

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description

      Adapter.Priority priority
      Sets the priority of the value() TypeAdapter.

    • Element Detail

      • value

        public abstract java.lang.Class<? extends TypeAdapter> value
        The TypeAdapter class to register into PaperParcel's type system.

      • priority

        public abstract Adapter.Priority priority

        Sets the priority of the value() TypeAdapter. If multiple TypeAdapters can handle the same type, priority is what decides which will be used (otherwise PaperParcel will use whichever it finds first). TypeAdapters with higher priority will be favoured.

        The default priority is Priority.LOW.

        Default:
        paperparcel.Adapter.Priority.LOW

      • nullSafe

        public abstract boolean nullSafe
        Return true if this type TypeAdapter can handle nulls or doesn't need to (i.e. the TypeAdapter is parcelling a non-nullable type). If this returns false (the default), then PaperParcel will do null-checking for you. Returning true from this method can help by preventing double (or completely unnecessary) null-checking.
        Default:
        false
